Take precautions with the jellyfish
Jul 2016 • Family
We recently finished a 3 day cruise . I am a doctor with a house in port Douglas so am well aware of stingers . We asked on the boat ( dragon legend) and looked on the website and were told there was no problem . We were swimming off the boat with everyone when my 10yo started screaming . She was covered in jellyfish stingers over 2 m long . She was wearing a one piece and rash vest but all her legs and arms were covered in stings that rapidly formed welts . We got her to the boat , the staff were hopeless doing everything wrong . Instead of carefully removing the tentacles they kept rubbing her legs with limes . I have included photos of her legs 1 hour after and a picture after 3 days . She was in excruciating pain for 4 hours and could not walk 3 days later .
The boats and tourist authorities are irresponsible and should warn people . So if you are swimming take precautions use a long sleeve rash vest and Lycra pants unless you want you holiday ruined.
